description:
Two SonarCloud minor findings:

**S7735** — `src/commands/set-md-field.ts:56`: Negated condition `!process.stdin.isTTY` in else-if. Swap the branches so the positive condition comes first:
```typescript
} else if (process.stdin.isTTY) {
  // Error: no content (was the else branch)
} else {
  // Read from stdin (was the else-if branch)
}
```

**S6551** — `src/services/azdo-client.ts:152`: `String(value)` where value is `unknown`. If value is an object, this produces `[object Object]`. Add explicit object handling:
```typescript
if (typeof value === 'object') {
  return JSON.stringify(value);
}
return String(value);
```

## Context
Phase 3: User Story 1 (P1) — MVP. Modify `get-item` to fall back to saved config defaults when no explicit flags and no git remote are available. This is the key integration that makes saved defaults useful.

Spec Reference: US1 acceptance scenarios 2, 3, 4 and FR-004.

## File Paths
- `src/commands/get-item.ts` (MODIFY)

## Implementation Details
Modify the `createGetItemCommand()` action handler to implement the 3-tier resolution order:

### Resolution Order (FR-004)
1. **Explicit `--org`/`--project` flags** (highest priority — existing behavior)
2. **Git remote auto-detection** via `detectAzdoContext()` (existing behavior)
3. **Saved defaults** from `loadConfig()` (NEW fallback)

### Current Flow (lines ~95-112)
```typescript
if (options.org && options.project) {
  context = { org: options.org, project: options.project };
} else {
  context = detectAzdoContext(); // throws if not in git repo or not Azure DevOps
}
```

### New Flow
```typescript
if (options.org && options.project) {
  context = { org: options.org, project: options.project };
} else {
  try {
    context = detectAzdoContext();
  } catch {
    // Fall back to saved config defaults
    const config = loadConfig();
    if (config.org && config.project) {
      context = { org: config.org, project: config.project };
    } else {
      throw new Error('Could not determine org/project. Use --org and --project flags, work from an Azure DevOps git repo, or run "azdo config set org/project".');
    }
  }
}
```

### Validation Update
The existing `hasOrg !== hasProject` check (lines 96-102) should remain — it validates that explicit flags come in pairs. The config fallback only activates when NEITHER flag is provided.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] When `--org`/`--project` flags provided: uses flags (existing behavior unchanged)
- [ ] When in Azure DevOps git repo without flags: uses git remote (existing behavior unchanged)
- [ ] When NOT in git repo and no flags, but config has org+project: uses config defaults
- [ ] When NOT in git repo, no flags, and config missing org or project: clear error with guidance
- [ ] Error message suggests `azdo config set` as a remediation
- [ ] Explicit flags override config (precedence test)
- [ ] Git remote overrides config (precedence test)
- [ ] All existing error handling preserved (AUTH_FAILED, NOT_FOUND, etc.)
- [ ] SC-004: Zero disruption when no settings configured

## Technical Notes
- Import `loadConfig` from `../services/config-store.js`
- The `detectAzdoContext()` call already throws on non-Azure-DevOps remotes or non-git directories
- Wrap the `detectAzdoContext()` call in try/catch to enable config fallback
- Constitution Principle V: minimal change — only add config fallback, don't restructure

Implement parseAzdoRemote(url: string): AzdoContext | null that extracts org and project from Azure DevOps git remote URLs. Must support all 5 cloud URL formats per research.md:

1. HTTPS current: https://dev.azure.com/{org}/{project}/_git/{repo}
2. HTTPS legacy: https://{org}.visualstudio.com/{project}/_git/{repo}
3. HTTPS legacy+DC: https://{org}.visualstudio.com/DefaultCollection/{project}/_git/{repo}
4. SSH current: git@ssh.dev.azure.com:v3/{org}/{project}/{repo}
5. SSH legacy: {org}@vs-ssh.visualstudio.com:v3/{org}/{project}/{repo}

Returns AzdoContext (org + project) on match, null for non-Azure URLs (GitHub, GitLab, etc.).
